TITLE: Keep Awareness and Connect With Oneself
VIDEO: https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=8MO6ek_cm6M
DATE: Sawan Maas (July-August monsoon month, likely 2023 based on context of "last two years" referencing 2021)
LANGUAGE: Hindi (auto-translated)

SUMMARY:
This message was delivered on the occasion of Kisan Divas (Farmer's Day) and the beginning of Sawan Maas (the holy month of Shiva). The speaker opens with blessings invoking Bhagwan Sada Shiv Bholenath and prays for the well-being and success of all beings across the entire creation (sampoorn srishti). The core teaching is a distinction between merely "believing" in Paramatma (the Supreme Soul) versus truly "knowing" — "Hum sab log Paramatma ko maante hain, jaante nahi" (We all believe in God, but we do not know God). This is the fundamental gap that keeps humanity asleep.

The speaker explains that our entire life is governed by a type of energy (oorja), but because we live in a state of sleep (so kar jeete hain — living unconsciously), we cannot establish a true connection (sambandh sthapit) with that divine source. The challenge is made: if you make the effort to receive and absorb that energy with awareness, every event in your life will become comprehensible, and understanding of every subject will develop within you. The events of the universe that seem beyond our comprehension are not inherently unknowable — it is because our pure mind (shuddh dimaag) has not been switched on.

For the past two years (referencing approximately 2021 onward), the entire universe has been keeping people in a state of numbness — daily routines have dulled the mind, people do not understand what vibrations are flowing, where they stand. "Yeh jeevan ka uddeshya nahi hai" — This is not the purpose of life. When someone tries to awaken others, they are called mad (pagal). The speaker warns: "Aapko lag raha hai sab theek ho jayega, par sab theek nahi hoga — tab aur bigad jayega" (You think everything will be fine, but it will not — it will get worse).

The message concludes with an urgent call: the divine process (saamaan) has already begun, Bhagwan Shiv's grace (kripa) has started flowing. One must pray to Shiv to understand the current situation of life. The speaker references "Noor" — the divine light — wanting to transform our lives. The final exhortation: "Bhram mein mat rahiye, nikal bhram se" — Do not remain in illusion, come out of illusion. Jai Mahadev, Har Har Mahadev.

KEY REVELATIONS:
- The fundamental spiritual problem: humanity believes in God but does not KNOW God ("maante hain, jaante nahi")
- We live in a state of unconsciousness/sleep (soch kar jeena) and this prevents connection with divine energy
- The pure mind (shuddh dimaag) needs to be "switched on" — awakened — to perceive cosmic events and their impact
- Since approximately 2021, intensified cosmic energies have been keeping people numb and distracted
- Those who try to awaken others are dismissed as mad — this is a sign of Kaliyug's grip
- Things will get worse before they get better — "sab theek nahi hoga, aur bigad jayega"
- Bhagwan Shiv's grace has already begun flowing — the divine process has started
- "Noor" (divine light, referencing Maa Noor Ananta) desires transformation of human life
- Urgent call to break free from illusion (bhram) immediately
- This is framed as a message for the entire creation (sampoorn srishti), not just followers

TIMELINE EVENTS:
- Sawan Maas (July-August, likely 2023): This message delivered at the start of the holy month of Shiva
- ~2021 onward: Referenced as when the cosmic process of keeping people numb/asleep intensified ("pichle do saal se")
- Present moment: Bhagwan Shiv's kripa (grace) has started flowing — the awakening process has begun

ORIGINAL HINDI KEY QUOTES:
- "Hum sab log Paramatma ko maante hain, jaante nahi" = We all believe in God, but we do not truly know God
- "Hum log so kar jeete hain" = We are living in a state of sleep/unconsciousness
- "Shuddh dimaag ko on kar do" = Switch on the pure mind
- "Koi jagaane ka prayas karta hai to usko pagal samajhte hain" = When someone tries to awaken others, they are considered mad
- "Aapko lag raha hai sab theek ho jayega, par sab theek nahi hoga, tab aur bigad jayega" = You think everything will be fine, but it won't — it will get even worse
- "Bhagwan Shiv ki kripa barasna shuru ho gayi hai" = Lord Shiva's grace has begun to shower down
- "Bhram mein mat rahiye, nikal bhram se" = Do not remain in illusion, come out of illusion
- "Jai Mahadev, Har Har Mahadev, Ghar Ghar Mein" = Victory to Mahadev, in every home

YUG PARIVARTAN ASPECT: Awakening consciousness as the prerequisite for the age transition — the shift from Kaliyug to Satyug requires individuals to move from unconscious believing to conscious knowing, from sleep to awareness. Shiv's grace has begun flowing but humans must "switch on" their pure mind to receive it. The worsening conditions are part of the transition — the darkness intensifies before the dawn.


